        }
      ],
      "returns": "str",
      "description": "Generate a human-readable token code.",
      "docstring": "Generate a human-readable token code.\n\nAlgorithm:\n1. Use cryptographically secure random (secrets module)\n2. Exclude ambiguous characters to prevent confusion:\n   - No 'O' (looks like 0)\n   - No 'I' or 'L' (look like 1)\n   - No '0' or '1' (ambiguous)\n3. Format with dashes for readability (XX-XX-XX)\n\nFormat: XX-XX-XX (6 characters in groups of 2)\nExample: \"X9-K4-M2\"\n\nArgs:\n    length: Total number of characters (default 6)\n\nReturns:\n    Formatted token string (e.g., \"X9-K4-M2\")\n    \nDesign Rationale:\n- Short enough to type manually (fallback when QR fails)\n- Long enough to prevent brute-force guessing (36^6 = 2.1B combinations)\n- Unambiguous characters reduce manual entry errors",
      "source": {
        "file": "services/token_generation.py",
        "line_start": 51,
        "line_end": 86
      },
