      "description": "Create signed JWT payload for QR code \"Magic Login\".",
      "docstring": "Create signed JWT payload for QR code \"Magic Login\".\n\nSecurity Design:\n1. JWT prevents tampering (HMAC-SHA256 signature)\n2. Expiration claim prevents replay attacks\n3. Issued-at claim for audit trail\n4. Type claim distinguishes from other JWTs\n\nThe QR code contains a signed token that can be validated server-side\nto prevent spoofing. This enables the mobile app to authenticate\nthe computer session via WebSocket handshake without exposing\nparticipant credentials.\n\nArgs:\n    token_code: The human-readable token (e.g., \"X9-K4-M2\")\n    session_id: Experiment session UUID\n    participant_id: Participant UUID\n    integration_id: Integration configuration UUID\n    expires_at: Token expiration timestamp\n\nReturns:\n    Signed JWT string for QR code embedding\n    \nExample JWT payload:\n    {\n        \"token\": \"X9-K4-M2\",\n        \"session_id\": \"uuid\",\n        \"participant_id\": \"uuid\",\n        \"exp\": 1737475200,\n        \"iat\": 1737468000,\n        \"type\": \"session_token\"\n    }",
      "source": {
